================================================================================

PROJECT INFORMATION
================================================================================

Project Name: MedEye v2.0
Subtitle: Medical Eye Disease Detection System

Description:
MedEye is a comprehensive deep learning and machine learning framework for 
automated detection and classification of eye diseases using medical retinal 
images. The system leverages state-of-the-art transfer learning models and 
traditional machine learning approaches to achieve high accuracy in clinical 
diagnostics.

Developer: Muhammad Daud
Created: 2026
Version: 2.0
License Type: MIT Open Source

================================================================================

KEY FEATURES
================================================================================

✓ Multiple Transfer Learning Models (EfficientNet, MobileNet, ResNet, etc.)
✓ Traditional Machine Learning Support (SVM, Random Forest)
✓ Comprehensive Data Validation and Preprocessing
✓ Production-Ready Error Handling and Logging
✓ Model Serialization and Deployment Support
✓ Extensive Testing Framework
✓ Detailed Documentation and API References

================================================================================

SUPPORTED MODELS
================================================================================

Transfer Learning Models:
- EfficientNetB3
- MobileNetV2
- DenseNet121
- ResNet50
- VGG16
- Xception
- InceptionV3

Traditional ML Models:
- Support Vector Machine (SVM)
- Random Forest Classifier
- Baseline Convolutional Neural Network

================================================================================

SUPPORTED DISEASES
================================================================================

The system is trained to detect and classify the following eye conditions:

1. Cataract - Clouding of the eye lens
2. Diabetic Retinopathy - Diabetes-related retinal damage
3. Glaucoma - Elevated intraocular pressure condition
4. Normal - Healthy retina (control class)

